word_mean_info__list.difference: 正式用词，多指以某事或活动达到预期目的而告终。
与complete基本同义，着重圆满地结束或完成已着手的事。
正式用词，强调一个过程的完成；也可指依靠努力达到一定目的，或取得一定的结果。
强调有一个空间和时间的限度，届时必须终止。书面语用词。
侧重指完成预定的任务或使某事完善，补足缺少的部分等。
最普通用词，着重事情的完成。也指某种活动因达到目的而自然结束或由于某种原因而突然中止。
普通用词，着重行为的终止或结束，不强调其目的。

bilingual.source: It's hard to finish it on time.
I'm going to finish high school first.
bilingual.target: 我打算先完成高中学业。

bilingual.source: We can finish our project next week.
bilingual.target: 我们可以下周完成我们的项目。

bilingual.source: It took me two hours to finish the work.
bilingual.target: 我花了两小时完成这项工作。

bilingual.source: I'll finish my high school education here.
bilingual.target: 我会在这里完成我的高中教育。

bilingual.source: Let's try our best to finish this task.
bilingual.target: 让我们尽最大努力去完成这个任务。

bilingual.source: It takes one month to finish a book report.
bilingual.target: 完成一份读书报告需要一个月。

bilingual.source: He said that he could finish the painting that day.
bilingual.target: 他说他那天可以完成这幅画。

list.abstract: finish英音：['finiʃ]美音：['fɪnɪʃ] 完成; 结束; 吃光; 使筋疲力尽n.结束; 结尾; 最后阶段; 抛光

yingyinNormal.en: And why not? 'Cause I didn't finish it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么？因为我还没完成。

yingyinNormal.en: Sir, I would like to finish our briefing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先生，我想先完成我们的讨论。

yingyinNormal.en: Nice racing, Padawan. You're the first to finish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 干得漂亮，我的绝地学徒。你是第一个完成的。

yingyinNormal.en: You had time to finish your little art project, but you didn't have time to finish your chores?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有时间完成你那个小艺术品，但是却没有时间做完家务吗？

yingyinNormal.en: We're waiting, sir. Waiting for what? Private Doss to finish praying for us, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们在等着，长官。等着啥？列兵多斯完成为我们的祈祷，长官。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, it's not just the meatballs, that's gonna finish the dish and make them look like lion heads.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了完成这道菜，让它们看起来像狮子头，光有肉丸不够。

yingyinNormal.en: So you have to finish what you're doing and you have to come home to her. You have to come home to us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以你要完成任务要回家，回到她身边，为了我们，你一定要回来。

yingyinNormal.en: Keep it simple, eyes on the ball, shoulders up, see your foot hit it, drive through the ball. Finish at your target!
yingyinNormal.zh: 简单点，看着球，抬起肩膀，看见你的脚踢到球，把球踢飞，完成目标！

yingyinNormal.en: Art class. This is you, Maya. Today, we finish our first paintings, and Mr. Jackson gets to see how talented you are.
yingyinNormal.zh: 美术课，是你表现自己的机会，玛雅，今天我们完成自己的第一幅作品，杰克逊老师会发现你多么有天赋。

yingyinNormal.en: Now to finish the salad, I've got here some dressing. So in here there's some pineapple juice, some lime juice, flavors of the sweet and sour. Lovely.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了完成沙拉，我要加些沙拉酱，倒一些菠萝汁，一些青柠汁，增加酸甜的味道。很好。

yingyinNormal.en: Here's my question. I successfully negotiated the release of Caroline and Melissa Miller. Then you stepped in. You didn't let me finish the job. Why?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想问你，我成功的谈判让卡洛琳和梅莉莎·米勒得以释放但你插手进你没让我完成任务，为什么？

yingyinNormal.en: I knew it wouldn't be safe to open the Chamber again while I was still at school, so I decided to leave behind a diary, preserving my 16-year-old self in its pages so that one day, I would be able to lead another to finish Salazar Slytherin's noble work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在我还待在学校的时候再打开密室实在是太冒险了，所以我决定留下我的日记，把十六岁的我保存在日记里头，直到有一天我能够引导另一个人来完成萨拉札斯莱特林的伟大使命。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets》

yingyinNormal.en: So, did you finish? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们做完了吗？没。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna go finish packing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要去收拾东西了。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll be outside when you finish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我去外面等你了。

yingyinNormal.en: People have got to finish their stories.
yingyinNormal.zh: 说故事的人得把故事说完。

yingyinNormal.en: A sprig or two of coriander. And finish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 加上一两片香菜，大功告成。

yingyinNormal.en: Dad, it's fine, I can finish the dusting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸爸，没关系了，我可以做扫灰。

yingyinNormal.en: Just finish that road and get outta here!
yingyinNormal.zh: 快点修完那条路，然后离开这里！

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it's time to finish it. Just a minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，那你现在就该写了。再等一下。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

sense_info_list.en: bring a task or activity to an end

examination_example.sentence: Maybe you haven't <highlight>finished</highlight> thinking the problem through, or you want to get a clearer sense of what the group thinks.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也许你还没有把这个问题考虑清楚，或者你想更清楚地了解这个群体的想法。

examination_example.sentence: When the EEOB was <highlight>finished</highlight>, it was the largest office building in Washington, with nearly 2 miles of black and white tiled corridors.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 艾森豪威尔行政办公大楼完工时，它有近两英里长的黑白瓷砖走廊，是华盛顿最大的办公楼。

examination_example.sentence: L. A. Unified has made the rule about homework mainly because poor students may have problems <highlight>finishing</highlight> their homework.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 洛杉矶联合学区制定了家庭作业的规定，主要是因为贫困学生在完成家庭作业方面可能有困难。

examination_example.sentence: There's always a constant fear of falling behind everyone else on the socially perpetuated "race to the <highlight>finish</highlight> line".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们总是担心在社会上永久不变的“冲向终点的比赛”中落后于人。

examination_example.sentence: But while young and old mostly agree on what constitutes the <highlight>finish</highlight> line of a fulfilling life, they offer strikingly different paths for reaching it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但尽管年轻一辈和老一辈在就什么构成成功人生的终点线这一问题上大体达成共识，他们为达到这一终点，提供了截然不同的路径。

word_usage.usage: 在接动名词时，finish doing sth.的意思是“结束做某事”，finish up doing sth.意思是“以某事的方式结束”

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 意为“结束”，表示在一个活动的连续过程中完成了最后的一步或阶段。
意为“完成；结束”表示积极地完成、完整地终结，一般指建筑、工程、书籍等的完成。
意为“实现，达到”，表示成功，强调完成的结果而不是过程。

word_usage.usage:
finish是瞬间动词，不能和表示一段时间的状语连用。
示例：我读完那本书已经一个星期了。
误 I have finished the book for a week.
正 I finished the book a week ago.
正 It is a week since I finished the book.

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 表成功, 强调完成的结果而不是过程。如：Because of his hard work, things are accomplished. (由于他的努力, 事情都已完成了。);也可指依靠努力达到一定目的, 或取得一定的结果。
表示积极的完成, 更具体地指建筑、工程等的完成。如：Has he complete his novel yet?(他的小说写完了吗？)
最常用, 后接动词的 -ing 形式, 表示在一个活动的连续过程中完成了最后的一步或阶段。如：I'll finish the job alone. (我要独自完成这项工作。)

word_usage.usage:
finish是瞬间动词，不能和表示一段时间的状语连用。
示例：我读完那本书已经一个星期了。
误 I have finished the book for a week.
正 I finished the book a week ago.
正 It is a week since I finished the book.

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 表成功，强调完成的结果而不是过程。如：Because of his hard work，things are accomplished. (由于他的努力，事情都已完成了。);也可指依靠努力达到一定目的，或取得一定的结果。
表示积极的完成，更具体地指建筑、工程等的完成。如：Has he complete his novel yet?(他的小说写完了吗？)
最常用，后接动词的 -ing 形式，表示在一个活动的连续过程中完成了最后的一步或阶段。如：I'll finish the job alone. (我要独自完成这项工作。)

word_usage.usage:
finish是瞬间动词，不能和表示一段时间的状语连用。
示例：我读完那本书已经一个星期了。
误 I have finished the book for a week.
正 I finished the book a week ago.
正 It is a week since I finished the book.

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 侧重指完成预定的任务或使某事完善，补足缺少的部分等。
与complete基本同义，着重圆满地结束或完成已着手的事。
最普通用词，着重事情的完成。也指某种活动因达到目的而自然结束或由于某种原因而突然中止。
普通用词，着重行为的终止或结束，不强调其目的。
